Preheat oven to 350Â°F with rack in middle. Butter a 9-inch pie plate. Pulse together graham crackers, almonds, and sugar in a food processor until finely ground. Transfer to a bowl and stir in butter. Press crumb mixture evenly onto bottom and up side of pie plate. Bake until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes. Cool completely. (Leave oven on.) Gently whisk together filling ingredients in a medium bowl until smooth and pour into crust. Bake until just set in center, 15 to 20 minutes. Cool completely (filling will set as it cools). Chill pie, loosely covered, at least 8 hours.